com.github.dm.jrt.invocation

Class FunctionInvocation<IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dm.jrt.invocation.TemplateInvocation<IN,OUT>
      • com.github.dm.jrt.invocation.FunctionInvocation<IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the input data type.
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Invocation<IN,OUT>

    public abstract class FunctionInvocation<IN,OUT>
extends TemplateInvocation<IN,OUT>
    Special abstract implementation that centralizes the routine invocation inside a single method, which gets called only when all the inputs are available.

    The implementing class may additionally override the invocation methods to specifically handle the object lifecycle. Note anyway that the superclass must be invoked in order to properly work.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 09/07/2014.
